arguments.prompt:
You are building a Blazor Web App for a veterinary clinic in /tmp/sv-08a240a37459449fa646f9db011dc326/VetClinic.

The project is already scaffolded with:
- `dotnet new blazor -int Server -ai -au Individual` (Interactive Server, Global, with Individual auth)
- .NET 11.0-preview.3
- SQLite database
- EF Core with Identity already configured
- Global interactivity via `<Routes @rendermode="PageRenderMode" />` in App.razor

## Your Task

Implement the full veterinary clinic management system. Here's what to do:

### 1. Domain Models — Create `/Data/Models/` directory with these files:

**Owner.cs:**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Owner
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string FirstName { get; set; } = "";
    public string LastName { get; set; } = "";
    public string Phone { get; set; } = "";
    public string Email { get; set; } = "";
    public List<Patient> Patients { get; set; } = [];
}
```

**Patient.cs:**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Patient
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Species { get; set; } = "";
    public string Breed { get; set; } = "";
    public DateOnly? DateOfBirth { get; set; }
    public int OwnerId { get; set; }
    public Owner Owner { get; set; } = null!;
    public List<TreatmentNote> TreatmentNotes { get; set; } = [];
    public List<Appointment> Appointments { get; set; } = [];
    public List<Invoice> Invoices { get; set; } = [];
}
```

**TreatmentNote.cs:**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class TreatmentNote
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public string Veterinarian { get; set; } = "";
}
```

**Appointment.cs:**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Appointment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime StartTime { get; set; }
    public int DurationMinutes { get; set; } = 30;
    public string Reason { get; set; } = "";
    public AppointmentStatus Status { get; set; } = AppointmentStatus.Scheduled;
}

public enum AppointmentStatus
{
    Scheduled,
    Completed,
    Cancelled
}
```

**Invoice.cs:**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Invoice
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int PatientId { get; set; }
    public Patient Patient { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public InvoiceStatus Status { get; set; } = InvoiceStatus.Pending;
    public List<InvoiceItem> Items { get; set; } = [];
    public List<Payment> Payments { get; set; } = [];
    public decimal Total => Items.Sum(i => i.Amount);
    public decimal AmountPaid => Payments.Sum(p => p.Amount);
    public decimal Balance => Total - AmountPaid;
}

public enum InvoiceStatus
{
    Pending,
    Paid,
    Cancelled
}
```

**InvoiceItem.cs:**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class InvoiceItem
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int InvoiceId { get; set; }
    public Invoice Invoice { get; set; } = null!;
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
}
```

**Payment.cs:**
```csharp
namespace VetClinic.Data.Models;

public class Payment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public int InvoiceId { get; set; }
    public Invoice Invoice { get; set; } = null!;
    public DateTime PaidAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public decimal Amount { get; set; }
    public string Method { get; set; } = ""; // Cash, Card, Check
}
```

### 2. Update ApplicationDbContext — Edit `/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs`:

Add DbSets for all models. Add `using VetClinic.Data.Models;`. Configure relationships in `OnModelCreating` (especially cascade delete rules — restrict deletes where it makes sense, e.g. can't delete an Owner if they have Patients).

### 3. Create a ClinicService — Create `/Services/ClinicService.cs`:

A scoped service that wraps DbContext access for all CRUD operations. Methods needed:
- Owners: GetAllOwners, GetOwner, CreateOwner, UpdateOwner
- Patients: GetAllPatients (with search/filter), GetPatient (include Owner, TreatmentNotes), CreatePatient, UpdatePatient
- TreatmentNotes: AddTreatmentNote
- Appointments: GetAppointmentsForDate, GetAppointmentsForWeek, GetAvailableSlots(DateTime date), CreateAppointment, RescheduleAppointment, CancelAppointment
- Invoices: GetAllInvoices (with filter by status), GetInvoice, CreateInvoice, AddInvoiceItem, RemoveInvoiceItem
- Payments: RecordPayment, GetPaymentHistory

For GetAvailableSlots: clinic hours are 8:00-18:00 with 30-min slots. A slot is unavailable if an appointment already occupies it.

### 4. Register the service in Program.cs:

Add `builder.Services.AddScoped<ClinicService>();` and the using for Services namespace.

### 5. Remove template pages:

Delete `Components/Pages/Counter.razor` and `Components/Pages/Weather.razor`.

### 6. Update Home.razor — Make it a dashboard:

Show summary stats: total patients, today's appointments, pending invoices. Add quick-action buttons to navigate to key pages.

### 7. Create Pages — All in `Components/Pages/`:

**Patients/Index.razor** (`@page "/patients"`):
- Search bar (filters by pet name or owner name)
- Table of patients with columns: Name, Species, Breed, Owner, Actions (View/Edit)
- "Register New Pet" button that opens an inline form or modal

**Patients/Details.razor** (`@page "/patients/{Id:int}"`):
- Pet info display with inline edit capability
- Owner info section
- Medical history (list of TreatmentNotes, newest first)
- "Add Treatment Note" form (textarea + veterinarian name, auto-fills from logged-in user display name)
- List of upcoming appointments for this patient

**Appointments/Index.razor** (`@page "/appointments"`):
- Date picker (defaults to today)
- Calendar/grid showing time slots 8:00-18:00 in 30-min increments
- Each slot shows: available (green, clickable to book), booked (shows patient name + reason)
- Clicking a booked slot shows details with Reschedule/Cancel buttons
- "New Appointment" form: select patient (searchable dropdown), pick date/time from available slots, reason

**Billing/Index.razor** (`@page "/billing"`):
- Filter by status (All/Pending/Paid/Cancelled)
- Table of invoices: Invoice #, Patient, Date, Total, Status, Actions
- "Create Invoice" button → form to select patient, add line items (description + amount), save

**Billing/InvoiceDetails.razor** (`@page "/billing/{Id:int}"`):
- Invoice header (patient, date, status)
- Line items table (editable — can add/remove items if status is Pending)
- Payment section: record new payment (amount, method dropdown: Cash/Card/Check)
- Payment history table

### 8. Update NavMenu:

Replace the template nav items with: Dashboard, Patients, Appointments, Billing. Use appropriate Bootstrap Icons or simple text.

### 9. Add [Authorize] attribute:

Add `@attribute [Authorize]` to all pages (not Account pages — those are already handled). The `_Imports.razor` should have `@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization`.

### 10. Create EF Migration:

Run `dotnet ef migrations add InitialClinicModels` from the project directory.

### 11. Add auto-migration at startup in Program.cs:

After `var app = builder.Build();` add:
```csharp
using (var scope = app.Services.CreateScope())
{
    var db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<ApplicationDbContext>();
    db.Database.Migrate();
}
```

### 12. Ensure the project builds:

Run `dotnet build` and fix any errors.

## Important Guidelines:
- Do NOT add `@rendermode` to any pages — global interactivity is already configured.
- Use `@inject ClinicService ClinicService` in pages to access data.
- Use `@inject AuthenticationStateProvider AuthStateProvider` where you need the logged-in user's name.
- Pages should use `OnInitializedAsync` to load data.
- Forms should use standard Blazor `EditForm` with `Model` and `OnValidSubmit`.
- For the appointment calendar, use a simple HTML table/grid — no JS libraries needed.
- Make the UI functional with Bootstrap classes (already included in the project).
- Don't overcomplicate CSS — use Bootstrap utilities.
- For RequireConfirmedAccount, set it to false so testing is easier (edit the existing line in Program.cs).

Work through this systematically. Create all files, ensure it builds.

